1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

2
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:23,640
 So we'll continue to preach on the letter to the Ephesians,

3
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:24,480
 chapter 3.

4
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:28,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

5
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:33,440
 So the title is Who Are You and How the Gospel Defines You.

6
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:35,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

7
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:37,760
 Let's read this scripture together.

8
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:40,160
 Let's do Chinese first.

9
00:00:40,160 --> 00:01:02,860
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

10
00:01:02,860 --> 00:01:04,960
 Well, let's read together Ephesians 3.

11
00:01:04,960 --> 00:01:08,840
 "For this reason, I, Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus,

12
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:11,600
 on behalf of you Gentiles, assuming

13
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:14,600
 that you have heard of the stewardship of God's grace

14
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:18,960
 that was given to me for you, how the mystery was made known

15
00:01:18,960 --> 00:01:24,440
 to me by revelation, as I have written briefly."

16
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:45,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

17
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:48,640
 Verse 4 and following, "When you read this,

18
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:52,880
 you can perceive my insight into the mystery of Christ,

19
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:57,200
 which was made known to the sons of men in other generations,

20
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:01,920
 as it has now been revealed to His holy apostles and prophets

21
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,280
 by the Spirit.

22
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:07,360
 This mystery is that the Gentiles are fellow heirs,

23
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:09,780
 members of the same body, partakers

24
00:02:09,780 --> 00:02:13,840
 of the promise in Christ Jesus through the gospel."

25
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:23,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

26
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:26,120
 The first question is, in which world you are living?

27
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:29,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

28
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:31,400
 I'm not asking you whether you believe in Jesus

29
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,680
 or whether you come to church.

30
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:35,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

31
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:39,720
 It's the question of which world are you living in right now?

32
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:43,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

33
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:47,320
 People may say, well, I'm living in this world in Chicago.

34
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:49,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

35
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:52,640
 But the scripture tells us there are two worlds simultaneously.

36
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:55,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

37
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:58,640
 So the old world is centered on ourselves.

38
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:01,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

39
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:03,680
 And then the new world's centered on Christ.

40
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:07,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

41
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:12,040
 Or put it another way, why do you live the way you do?

42
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:14,400
 And why do you do this?

43
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:20,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

44
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:22,680
 Or think about every decision that you make.

45
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:28,440
 And there's a question for you is, why do I do those things?

46
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

47
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,520
 And we have to ask this question often.

48
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:35,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

49
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:39,680
 And our answer to this question is that we want to live better.

50
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:44,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

51
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:48,720
 And then everything's like revolving around ourselves.

52
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:52,600
 And the faith has become a footnote.

53
00:03:52,600 --> 00:04:04,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

54
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,200
 And then we want to turn to the scripture today

55
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:08,800
 and to challenge ourselves, like Paul reminds us.

56
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:11,400
 Are we living in the gospel-centered world,

57
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:14,480
 or are we stuck in the old world centered on ourselves?

58
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:16,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

59
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,640
 OK, so first two verses.

60
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:20,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

61
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,480
 So the main point is, who controls your reality?

62
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:30,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

63
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:33,400
 And Paul described himself and introduced himself.

64
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,920
 He says, not an apostle.

65
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:40,640
 He introduced himself as a prisoner of Christ Jesus.

66
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:49,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

67
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,760
 And we talk about Paul.

68
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,480
 When he wrote this letter, he was not

69
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:55,240
 on the shore of Mediterranean resort,

70
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:57,800
 and he was in prison for the gospel.

71
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:01,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

72
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,920
 And if you think you were Paul, and how would you

73
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,880
 introduce yourself when you write the letter?

74
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:13,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

75
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:16,280
 And you may introduce yourself, Paul,

76
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:20,080
 I am the apostle chosen by God.

77
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:24,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

78
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:28,840
 And Paul says, I am prisoner of Christ Jesus.

79
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

80
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:36,320
 And it's very strange that he introduced himself like this.

81
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,760
 No problem.

82
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:39,280
 I got it.

83
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,400
 Oops, sorry.

84
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,120
 OK, here you go.

85
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

86
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:48,280
 So to the Romans, [SPEAKING CHINESE]

87
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:51,360
 Paul is a totally defeated person.

88
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:53,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

89
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,280
 From the perspective of the world, from the Romans.

90
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:58,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

91
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:01,520
 And if Paul sees himself in the Roman way,

92
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:03,680
 and he would pity on himself.

93
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

94
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:09,480
 But from another perspective, from the gospel perspective.

95
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:17,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

96
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:22,280
 And he was not a defeat, and he was chosen by God.

97
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:24,600
 And part of the plan of God is for him

98
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:27,080
 to be in prison for the gospel.

99
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:36,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

100
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:38,080
 And not only he was in prison for the gospel,

101
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,200
 he was chosen by God.

102
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:43,080
 Even in full suffering, he's advancing the gospel.

103
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:50,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

104
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:52,960
 So as you can see, it's the same circumstances in the world,

105
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:57,400
 but it's a completely, totally different perspectives and interpretations.

106
00:06:57,400 --> 00:07:10,740
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

107
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:13,600
 And if we come from a very narrow perspective,

108
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,400
 and we see Paul's life of suffering in prison,

109
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:20,160
 and we'll think that, OK, maybe suffering is always good.

110
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:35,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

111
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:39,760
 So the real question is not whether he is in prison now or he's suffering.

112
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:42,680
 The main question is, who is narrating your life?

113
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:45,120
 Who is defining your life and circumstances?

114
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:48,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

115
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:50,200
 So that's the main point here.

116
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,480
 Who controls your reality?

117
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,600
 How you see reality?

118
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:57,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

119
00:07:57,200 --> 00:08:00,040
 And he said it's not the circumstances that define him,

120
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:04,760
 but it's the Christ, Jesus, the Lord defines him.

121
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:15,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

122
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:19,640
 So sometimes we need to think about our own lives.

123
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:23,120
 We define ourselves by our jobs, our career, our income,

124
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,680
 our reputation, our achievement.

125
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:29,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

126
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:32,460
 And the question of the gospel confronts us

127
00:08:32,460 --> 00:08:36,640
 is that, why are we doing what we do?

128
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,960
 And who do we belong to?

129
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

130
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:43,000
 So who is defining our life?

131
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

132
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:48,560
 It's not the world, it's Christ to define you.

133
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:52,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

134
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:55,080
 So the first point is, we have to understand Christ, Jesus

135
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,600
 defines our identity.

136
00:08:56,600 --> 00:09:01,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

137
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:04,560
 So then we can come to see Paul's suffering

138
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,280
 from this perspective.

139
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:15,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

140
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:19,000
 So this extends to the providence of God in our lives,

141
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,400
 not just the good things, but also the difficult things,

142
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,600
 like Paul's imprisonment and suffering.

143
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:29,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

144
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:33,280
 And you can see the imprisonment and suffering of Paul

145
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,880
 is a bad thing, but in the providence of God,

146
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,360
 it can be a good thing.

147
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:49,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

148
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:52,560
 So the providence of God is not just permitting something bad

149
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:56,000
 happen in our lives, but according to Paul,

150
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,760
 in Romans 8, that everything God works together

151
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:04,720
 for the goodness of his kingdom.

152
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:08,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

153
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:12,360
 So that's how Paul interprets his suffering.

154
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:27,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

155
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:30,320
 So when life is not going well for us,

156
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,280
 how do we define our life?

157
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:35,240
 And according to the folk religion,

158
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:37,240
 or in Christian's worldview, it's

159
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:41,080
 the luck and the fortune or circumstances that defines us.

160
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:43,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

161
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:48,720
 But God says in the Bible, Christ controls everything.

162
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:51,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

163
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:55,120
 So things happening in our lives are not because of randomness,

164
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:57,840
 but there is a plan in him.

165
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:05,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

166
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:10,640
 And so Paul is talking about not only the mission that he has,

167
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:13,000
 but he received a stewardship from God.

168
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:20,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

169
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:25,480
 So Paul is suffering, but he is suffering not forgetting

170
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:28,760
 that God is giving him the stewardship and this mission

171
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:30,560
 to deliver the gospel.

172
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:44,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

173
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:48,960
 So this stewardship is entrusting something important,

174
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:52,480
 just like if I go away for a long trip

175
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:55,520
 and I entrust the message to Paul, then Paul

176
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:59,920
 has to relay this message, important message, to Wendy.

177
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:03,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

178
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:07,320
 So Paul is not saying that his job is his own job,

179
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:10,840
 but it's God's entrusting this assignment to him.

180
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:14,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

181
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:19,440
 So you think about your own life is not your own ownership

182
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:24,120
 at all, it's God giving you the stewardship for your life.

183
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:32,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

184
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,440
 And if you think about our lives,

185
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:39,160
 we are not the owner of our own possessions,

186
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:43,000
 but God is entrusting to us the career, the children,

187
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,800
 including our wealth, everything,

188
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:48,120
 and we are just stewards and managers.

189
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:53,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

190
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,160
 And for a good steward, he understands

191
00:12:56,160 --> 00:13:00,200
 he's being entrusted something important from the owner.

192
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:07,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

193
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:10,760
 You see, so often we come to God and we just

194
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,080
 want to receive blessing and good things from him.

195
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:18,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

196
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:23,120
 But Paul is emphasizing, I have received the stewardship

197
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,960
 from God himself.

198
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:31,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

199
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:35,560
 And to verses 3 to 5, Paul is talking about the gospel

200
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:36,720
 he is preaching.

201
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:40,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

202
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:44,080
 He said God revealed the mystery of the gospel to him.

203
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:48,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

204
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:51,800
 So the mystery here is talking about the gospel.

205
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:54,640
 It was hidden before, but now because of Christ,

206
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,680
 it was revealed.

207
00:13:55,680 --> 00:14:00,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

208
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,200
 And how did Paul figure out the gospel?

209
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,800
 He did not do it from his own personal research

210
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:08,600
 or from another person, but from direct revelation of God.

211
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:17,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

212
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:20,120
 And the term revelation, what does it mean?

213
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:23,760
 It means-- it does not mean something mysterious,

214
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:26,280
 but it means something that was covered before,

215
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:28,560
 but now it's uncovered.

216
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:39,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

217
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:43,320
 So just like the cage back there was originally

218
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:46,480
 covered by a curtain, and if you take away the curtain,

219
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:49,680
 then now it's uncovered, and you can see what's inside.

220
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:57,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

221
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,120
 And the same way for the gospel.

222
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,280
 The gospel is not discovered by men.

223
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,080
 It is uncovered by God.

224
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:06,160
 It's revealed what's inside, and now we know the gospel.

225
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:11,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

226
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:14,480
 And God revealed the gospel to Paul.

227
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:21,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

228
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:25,360
 And of course, God also revealed to Paul and other apostles,

229
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:28,880
 but it is the direct revelation from God.

230
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:37,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

231
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:41,840
 So this revelation is already complete in Christ Jesus.

232
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:44,840
 So Paul has already received this revelation.

233
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,520
 Now, the later generations of Christians,

234
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:49,400
 we may have illumination from the Spirit,

235
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:52,240
 but we don't have new revelation.

236
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:57,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

237
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:59,680
 So the gospel is not invented by men.

238
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:02,280
 It is directly revealed by God.

239
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:11,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

240
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:14,280
 So humanity can figure out the existence of God

241
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:16,280
 from the general revelation from the creation,

242
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:20,600
 but sometimes it is the will, and it's not very correct.

243
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:35,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

244
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:40,080
 And you remember, recently, NASA has sent four astronauts

245
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:42,280
 to fly around the moon, and one came back,

246
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:46,480
 and there were four of them, and one was a Christian,

247
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:49,200
 and he came back, and he was baptized.

248
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:58,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

249
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:01,640
 And he was seeing, when he traveled around the moon

250
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:07,800
 and saw the space, and he said it's very impossible for us

251
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:10,840
 to deny the existence of creator.

252
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:15,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

253
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:19,400
 But nature can point you to the existence of the creator.

254
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:28,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

255
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:31,880
 But if you really need to understand or know God,

256
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,920
 you have to depend on not your own consciousness,

257
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:38,800
 but not through creation, but from the direct revelation

258
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,120
 from God.

259
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:47,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

260
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:50,560
 And the special revelation is Christ Jesus himself,

261
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:53,320
 and also the Word of God we find in the Bible.

262
00:17:53,320 --> 00:18:05,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

263
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:09,640
 So you think about it, without God directly revealing himself

264
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,800
 in the gospel, in Christ Jesus, there's

265
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:15,560
 no way man can figure out a crucified man is

266
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:16,960
 the center of the gospel.

267
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:28,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

268
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:31,360
 And you think about a God who dies on the cross

269
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:36,720
 and who fails, and this is totally foolish,

270
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:39,560
 according to human logic.

271
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:46,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

272
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:51,400
 In the Qing dynasty, there was a statement called Li Hongzhang,

273
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:55,960
 and he once said that there is no way that he could understand

274
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:59,520
 why the Western people would believe in such a defeated

275
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:01,160
 Christ Jesus.

276
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:12,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

277
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:19,280
 So as you can see, the salvation plan of God

278
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:21,280
 is against human logic.

279
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:27,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

280
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:32,600
 So the essence of the gospel is that God is coming to find you

281
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:35,240
 on the cross of Jesus.

282
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:43,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

283
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,720
 And he said this revelation of gospel

284
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:48,320
 is already a shadow in the Old Testament.

285
00:19:48,320 --> 00:20:02,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

286
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:05,840
 And you think about the Old Testament in the Abraham

287
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:08,480
 promise, God has already told him

288
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:11,120
 you will be blessed with many, many children and many, many

289
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:11,840
 people.

290
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,160
 And then in the prophecy of Isaiah,

291
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:18,480
 he was already prophesized there was some savior or servant

292
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,840
 will come to save us.

293
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:44,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

294
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:49,960
 And you think about the Old Testament's shadows, and it's just the sketch

295
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:53,640
 of the gospel, like driving into Chicago.

296
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:55,680
 Far away, you can see the skyline of a city,

297
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,760
 but it's very blurry on the horizon.

298
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:00,440
 Only when you arrive downtown and you come to downtown,

299
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:03,440
 you will see it clearly.

300
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:12,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

301
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:15,360
 So from the Old Testament, you can see these shadows.

302
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:17,040
 You can see the shadow of the gospel.

303
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:20,400
 But until Christ Jesus came, the mystery is revealed.

304
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,640
 And he came, and he died, and he rose again.

305
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:25,520
 And the spirit is poured out to his people.

306
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:29,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

307
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:31,800
 So you see, what is revealed is Christ Jesus.

308
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,000
 And what is the gospel?

309
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,320
 The gospel is Christ Jesus himself.

310
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:38,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

311
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:43,480
 So God gave us Jesus Christ, his son, and that is the gospel.

312
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:53,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

313
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:57,960
 So the third point is that what is this mystery of the gospel?

314
00:21:57,960 --> 00:22:04,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

315
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:07,960
 So Paul is saying the mystery is that now, in Christ Jesus,

316
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:11,160
 even Gentiles can become part of the people of God.

317
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:15,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

318
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:18,920
 And to be the share heir of the promises

319
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:21,680
 is a new identity.

320
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:25,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

321
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:28,960
 So we are not sojourner outside of God's kingdom,

322
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:30,680
 but we are being included.

323
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:34,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

324
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,720
 And it's not because our performance,

325
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,200
 we can earn the salvation of God.

326
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:39,440
 But it's all because of grace of God.

327
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:49,060
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

328
00:22:49,060 --> 00:22:52,720
 And the Bible tells us we Gentiles are the fellow heirs.

329
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:55,960
 And our identity has changed, and we become one people.

330
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:57,680
 And we can share the blessing of God.

331
00:22:57,680 --> 00:23:08,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

332
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:12,560
 So this identity informs us that even now,

333
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:15,520
 our identity is the kingdom of the people to come.

334
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:19,440
 So we live now, but we belong to the kingdom to come.

335
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:36,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

336
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:40,040
 And it's all past tense description for our identity.

337
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:43,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

338
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:45,900
 And you think about it, OK, we have not ascended to heaven

339
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:48,400
 like Christ, but how is that possible?

340
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:53,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

341
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:55,880
 But Paul is saying this new identity informs you

342
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:59,160
 you have already been united with Christ,

343
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:01,640
 and he has rose and ascended to heaven.

344
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:03,520
 So are we.

345
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:09,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

346
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,200
 So Paul is saying in the Ephesians

347
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:14,080
 that the gospel has formed a new people, a new group,

348
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:15,280
 and a new humanity.

349
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:25,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

350
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:28,240
 So in conclusion, for the three points,

351
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:32,160
 the gospel is not making us more successful or making us more,

352
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:34,040
 but to redefining us.

353
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:42,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

354
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:45,160
 So the gospel is not simply just add on to our lives,

355
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:50,260
 but to reconfigure and redefine our own identity, who we are.

356
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:56,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

357
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:57,760
 And because of the gospel, we are

358
00:24:57,760 --> 00:25:00,200
 being brought to a new creation, a new world,

359
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:05,120
 and that is in united with Christ Jesus himself.

360
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:14,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

361
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:16,240
 So the first point, you remember,

362
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:19,040
 God is bringing us to a new world.

363
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:22,320
 And so who are we in Christ?

364
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:26,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

365
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:29,960
 So our life is not defined by our success or our failure,

366
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:33,640
 but we are defined solely on Christ Jesus himself.

367
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:43,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

368
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:48,000
 So the world is telling you, you have to earn the identity.

369
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,760
 You have to earn the success.

370
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:53,680
 But the gospel informs us in a radically different way.

371
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:56,760
 It says, in Christ Jesus, we belong to God.

372
00:25:56,760 --> 00:26:00,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

373
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:01,960
 So understand who we are.

374
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:05,240
 And the second question is, who do we live for?

375
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:07,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

376
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:10,840
 And the gospel informs us we are not living for ourselves,

377
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,720
 but for Christ Jesus.

378
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:19,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

379
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,400
 So you think about the life of Paul.

380
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:24,840
 He was a super orthodox rabbi.

381
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:26,240
 And he came to know Christ.

382
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:29,480
 And his journey of life, the direction of life,

383
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:30,720
 has totally changed.

384
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:35,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

385
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:38,240
 So in a worldly perspective, he's messed up his life.

386
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:41,000
 But from God's perspective, he is directing

387
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:44,920
 to a new and right direction.

388
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:55,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

389
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:59,200
 But that does not mean we abandon our ordinary life.

390
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:02,360
 We don't work, or we don't go about managing our lives.

391
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:04,880
 But the center has changed for our lives.

392
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:08,000
 Our center has shifted because of Christ.

393
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:21,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

394
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:24,720
 So the gospel informs us we have belief in Christ.

395
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:28,280
 And we are being entrusted with the gospel.

396
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:38,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

397
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,800
 Just like Paul has a baby and a child.

398
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:43,640
 And he's being entrusted with a precious life.

399
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:47,800
 And also with it, a lot of suffering and responsibilities.

400
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:59,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

401
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:02,240
 And the point is, we have received

402
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:05,120
 a lot of different responsibilities and roles

403
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:05,720
 in our lives.

404
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:08,960
 But the gospel has challenged us,

405
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:11,640
 confronted us, that we are being entrusted with something

406
00:28:11,640 --> 00:28:12,880
 that is important.

407
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:15,600
 And that is the center of the gospel.

408
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:25,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

409
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:27,800
 So the first question is, who are we?

410
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:28,640
 We are in Christ.

411
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:29,760
 And who are we living for?

412
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,280
 We are living for Christ.

413
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:32,840
 And the third question is, how do you

414
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:35,200
 see the body of Christ, the community of faith?

415
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:50,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

416
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:54,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

417
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:56,000
 You speak English or Cantonese or Mandarin.

418
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,280
 And you have your own group.

419
00:28:57,280 --> 00:29:08,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

420
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:11,480
 Or you're rich or I'm poor, so we're different.

421
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:18,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

422
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:21,680
 But the gospel has formed a totally new humanity.

423
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:24,720
 It's not because you're better or I'm poor

424
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:27,000
 or because you're stronger or weaker.

425
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:30,040
 But we are new people in Christ.

426
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:35,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

427
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:38,600
 So the city of man is ordered by division and separation.

428
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:42,680
 But the city of God is united in Christ.

429
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:48,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

430
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:51,160
 So brothers and sisters, we may call ourselves Christians.

431
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:53,760
 But we may be still living for ourselves.

432
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:57,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

433
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:58,440
 When we come to church, probably we

434
00:29:58,440 --> 00:30:00,920
 are still living in the old world.

435
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:06,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

436
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:08,800
 So Christ comes to our lives.

437
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:11,880
 And asking ourselves, the core of our identity

438
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:15,080
 has to be shift from ourselves to Christ.

439
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:18,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

440
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:20,400
 And we ask ourselves, at the bottom of our hearts,

441
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:23,200
 are we living for ourselves or living for Christ?

442
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:26,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

443
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:28,880
 Or whatever God has entrusted to us,

444
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:32,560
 and we are avoiding it or trying to escape or run away

445
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:34,400
 or being faithful.

446
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:38,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

447
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:41,760
 And in the church, are we building up for the--

448
00:30:41,760 --> 00:30:42,960
 building the unity?

449
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:47,000
 Or we are constantly comparing ourselves to other people?

450
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

451
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:51,280
 And let's pray together.

452
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:54,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

453
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:58,400
 God, we want to give you thanks, because you gave us your word.

454
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:02,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

455
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:05,160
 And we pray that, just like Paul, how he sees himself.

456
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:08,680
 And we use the same perspective to see ourselves.

457
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:10,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

458
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,680
 And why are we living?

459
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:14,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

460
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:17,520
 And we are not just living for ourselves, but living for you.

461
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:18,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

462
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:20,200
 Living in the gospel.

463
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:22,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

464
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:25,200
 And day to day, we live for your glory.

465
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:26,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

466
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:28,800
 So we pray in Jesus Christ.

467
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,840
 Amen.

468
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:32,240
 Thank you, Paul.

469
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:34,240
 Well, let's give him a hand.

